reviewText: Quizes are flawed, i.e. software doesn't recognize the right answers.

O​ne of the best lectures I have attended in the applied mathematics related to numerical analysis in optimization and data science. Although the teaching approach is simple, it is assumed that the candidate student wants just to focus or clarify specific mathematical questions in a more advanced perspective later. More abstraction exists in other mathematical courses. Here it is a fast and exact discussion on several topics for specific target. Perfect job!
